 "methodology_notes": [
  "Fees = DefiLlama protocol 'fees' adapters (gross fees paid by users), NOT holder revenue; see holder_revenue_note per protocol for who actually captures it.",
  "fees_2023 is the calendar-2023 sum; only computed where the fee adapter's history reaches back to Jan 2023 (fees_reaches_2023=true). fees_growth_x = fees_ttm / fees_2023.",
  "Price 'return' uses the 2023-01-01 close where the token existed; for post-2023 launches (price_from_inception=true) the base is the first recorded trade, which is frequently an airdrop/listing peak and makes returns look worse \u2014 a launch-timing artifact, not necessarily fundamentals.",
  "l1_return_same_window compares the home L1 token's return over the EXACT same window as each app token (fair matched-window fat-protocol test).",
  "Adapter methodology shifts (protocols re-scoping what counts as a 'fee') can create step-changes in the series unrelated to real activity (the LINK-style artifact); treat extreme multiples with caution.",
  "Survivorship: this is the protocols alive and adaptered in 2023-2026; dead 2021-era names (e.g. many yield farms) are absent, so the cohort is biased upward."
